data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction can be replaced with simple imperative code:

```csharp
// After (.NET 10)
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery is no longer needed (or accepted).

---

### 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified/use full paths

Two changes hit you:

- **Duplicate property names** (`ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a numeric suffix to disambiguate.
- **Nested complex types** (`Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City`) now map to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of the old `BillingAddress_City`.

Both will generate a migration renaming columns. To **preserve your existing column names**, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on that interface now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← add this
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** method signatures on your implementation (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) — they all gained this parameter.
